body:
@bertholdreinwald Thank you for reviewing.

To determine the libraries to add to the in-memory jar, I added libraries one at a time and rebuilt each time as each 'class not found' exception occurred when I ran the JMLCExample in a separate project using the built in-memory jar. I repeated this process until the example ran with no exceptions, so I think the list of included libraries is about as minimal as possible given the current set-up. Would you like me to investigate the 6M increase in size to try to determine where the increase is coming from?

I agree that readScript() for the mtx data is a little strange. I'll update the examples with your suggestions.
